<h1>Backup & Restore</h1>
<p>Learn how to backup and restore all your AgeMap data as a ZIP file.</p>

<h2>What's Included</h2>
<p>The backup file contains the following data:</p>
<ul>
  <li>All registered people</li>
  <li>Groups and family relationship data</li>
  <li>Profile photos</li>
  <li>Moment records and attached photos</li>
  <li>App settings (notification time, reminder range, etc.)</li>
</ul>

<h2>Backup</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Go to Settings.</li>
  <li>In the Data Management section, tap <strong>Backup</strong>.</li>
  <li>Choose a save location.</li>
  <li>The filename is auto-generated as <code>agemap_backup_DATE.zip</code>.</li>
  <li>A progress indicator will be shown. You'll be notified when it's complete.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Restore</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Go to Settings.</li>
  <li>In the Data Management section, tap <strong>Restore</strong>.</li>
  <li>Select a previously created backup ZIP file.</li>
  <li>A confirmation dialog will appear. Tap <strong>Restore</strong> to proceed.</li>
  <li>The app will automatically restart after restoration is complete.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Transferring Data to a New Device</h2>
<ol>
  <li>Run Backup on your old device.</li>
  <li>Transfer the backup ZIP file via Google Drive, email, etc.</li>
  <li>Install AgeMap on your new device.</li>
  <li>Download the backup file to the new device and run Restore.</li>
</ol>

<h2>Important Notes</h2>
<ul>
  <li>Restoring will replace all current data with the backup file data.</li>
  <li>This action cannot be undone. It is recommended to backup your current data before restoring.</li>
  <li>Store backup files in external storage like Google Drive or email for safety against device loss.</li>
  <li>Backup file size may be large if you have many photos.</li>
</ul>

